al Islamophobia and its manifestations in Europe, Asia, the Middle East, and regions beyond and in between. Through trenchant analysis and direct testimony from Muslims on the ground, Beydoun interrogates how Islamophobia acts as a unifying global thread of state and social bigotry, instigating both liberal and right-wing hate-mongering. Whether imposed by way of hijab bans in France, state-sponsored hate speech and violence in India, or the network of concentration camps in China, Islamophobia unravels into distinct systems of demonization and oppression across the post-9/11 geopolitical landscape. Lucid and poignant, The New Crusades reveals that Islamophobia is not only a worldwide phenomenon—it stands as one of the world's last bastions of acceptable hate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aIslamophobia. 0aMuslimszNon-Islamic countries. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / General.2bisacsh  aAfrica.  aAsia.  aEurope.  aIslamophobia around the world.  aMiddle East.  aMideast.  aPacific.  acrusade.  acurrent affairs.  ademonization.  ageopolitics.  aglobal War on Terror.  aoppression.  apolicing.  aprofiling.  aviolence on muslim community.  axenophobia.1 aCrenshaw, Kimberlé, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520976061?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520976061423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520976061/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY